after you've read a good book do you replay parts of it in your mind okay so i just finished this book called the pact by jodi picoult last night and i can't stop thinking about it this book is an tragic love story and i keep re playing parts of it in my head i can't help feeling a sense of longing for the type of love that these two people share i'm constantly feeling upset as if i were one of the main characters i was just curious if other people feel the same way after they've read a book that they were truly passionate about yes books and movies do that to you they get stuck in your head almost like a song Beauty and the Beast (1991 film) Taxi Driver The Catcher in the Rye Desire (album) A Course In Miracles Time Out of Mind Love Kodocha One Tree Hill (TV series) The Amber Spyglass The Sound and the Fury Jon Secada Care Bears Spice Girls The Secret of NIMH Goldstein's book Ramakrishna The Red Pony The Brothers Karamazov The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Micronauts Bat Lash The Raven Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Witches (Discworld) M (James Bond) Pitaten Francis Hutcheson (philosopher) Fancy Crane Sydney Riot of 1879 Cliff Richard Miss Saigon Charles Dickens Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Animal Farm Witchcraft David Hume Blood on the Tracks Asperger syndrome Michel Henry Iago Camp Lazlo It's All Gone Pete Tong Socrates Jody Watley Alice's Adventures in Wonderland Shaggy dog story D.N. Angel Transactional analysis The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Thinks ... Mina Mongoose American Psycho Kurt Cobain John Howard Yoder Empathy Discworld Nineteen Eighty-Four Reefer Madness Nicomachean Ethics Mulholland Drive (film) The Chronicles of Narnia Theory of conduct Johnny Appleseed Neil Gaiman Alignment (role-playing games) Daredevil Year of the Spider The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film) Timpani Children's literature Hitchhiking Oroonoko About a Boy Anti-hero Yesterday (song) The Inside The Lovely Bones Johnny the Homicidal Maniac Garry Kasparov Forbidden Planet 